And there's a lot of cultural standards and norms that may apply.

00:15.880 --> 00:22.300
So I'm going to tell you what has worked for me and also what I have seen work for others.

00:22.300 --> 00:26.830
Underneath it all there are some few basic principles that can be applied.

00:27.070 --> 00:34.390
And this common theme and common tactics is something that will help you as well but keep that in mind.

00:34.390 --> 00:36.280
Cultures do play a big role here.

00:37.360 --> 00:39.010
All right let's get started.

00:39.310 --> 00:44.730
If you we're asked What salary do you want in an interview what do you say.

00:45.740 --> 00:48.470
Think about this for a second you can pause the video.

00:48.530 --> 00:53.280
What will be your answer when somebody asks you What are your salary expectations.

00:53.300 --> 00:54.760
All right you thought about it.

00:54.860 --> 00:56.140
This is what I would say.

00:56.450 --> 01:01.080
Well I know that the average software developer in Silicon Valley.

01:01.130 --> 01:06.560
Let's say I'm applying there makes roughly a hundred and twenty thousand a year.

01:06.590 --> 01:09.500
So I think that's a good place for us to start.

01:09.510 --> 01:10.430
That was it.

01:10.470 --> 01:12.520
That's what I would say.

01:12.720 --> 01:14.740
Now why is that.

01:14.820 --> 01:18.610
And this goes to my very first point.

01:18.680 --> 01:21.260
You don't want to end the conversation.

01:21.260 --> 01:22.410
You see what I did here.

01:22.510 --> 01:28.650
I didn't actually answer their question and say well I want 90000 per year.

01:28.670 --> 01:36.200
All I did was do something called anchoring where I tell them this is where we want our conversation

01:36.200 --> 01:37.280
to start.

01:37.730 --> 01:43.700
I want the conversation to start around the number 130000 a year and I'm not saying that this is what

01:43.700 --> 01:50.100
I want to get paid this is just simply me starting our conversation so that we can talk about things.

01:50.210 --> 01:56.440
All I said was the average software engineer in negotiation especially when it comes to salary negotiation

01:56.870 --> 02:00.840
you're going to want to give an actual number to end the conversation.

02:02.290 --> 02:09.370
Instead you want to keep the conversation going by giving something like an industry average and make

02:09.370 --> 02:14.670
it clear that you're merely starting the negotiation here and not ending it.

02:14.980 --> 02:17.590
And that's how we start negotiating.

02:17.590 --> 02:24.550
Let's talk about the next point we want to give a reason for everything because we all know the problem

02:24.550 --> 02:26.800
with negotiating right.

02:26.890 --> 02:33.010
If you say you want more salary or more vacation time we kind of sound greedy.

02:33.040 --> 02:39.400
We don't want to sound greedy and we're money hungry and that all we do is care about these numbers

02:39.430 --> 02:43.680
and ourselves as we know nobody really likes greedy people right.

02:43.690 --> 02:46.150
As a matter of fact this is the main reason people don't negotiate.

02:46.150 --> 02:50.760
They just don't want to offend people and seem mean and hungry just for money.

02:50.830 --> 02:54.030
Instead you want to give a reason for everything.

02:54.040 --> 02:58.810
For example if somebody gives you an offer and this is something that will talk and lead on videos and

02:58.810 --> 03:04.920
says hey we are going to offer you $80000 a year what do you think.

03:05.010 --> 03:11.650
Are you in or are you at instead of saying well no I need more time.

03:11.790 --> 03:15.030
Maybe you could say something along the lines of.

03:15.050 --> 03:16.620
Well thank you very much for this offer.

03:16.620 --> 03:19.670
It's very generous and I'm very excited.

03:19.680 --> 03:21.280
Potentially working with your company.

03:21.360 --> 03:27.260
However this is a big family decision and I'm looking to work at a company for many years.

03:27.390 --> 03:33.990
So I would like to discuss this with my wife or my partner and have some time to make sure that there's

03:34.010 --> 03:36.210
something we are both comfortable with.

03:37.180 --> 03:38.480
And you see what I did here.

03:38.680 --> 03:42.620
I just asked for more time or to not give an answer right away.

03:42.760 --> 03:50.080
Perhaps over the phone and instead speak to my partner and all I did was give a reason why I'm doing

03:50.080 --> 03:55.770
things I'm not being selfish I don't want more time just strictly for myself.

03:55.840 --> 04:02.640
This is something that I'm doing because I have somebody else that is involved in the decision.

04:02.740 --> 04:06.600
And by giving a reason like that as an interviewer that makes sense right.

04:06.610 --> 04:10.510
I mean the interviewer will be doing the same in your shoes.

04:11.130 --> 04:12.600
Let's talk about the next point.

04:13.320 --> 04:18.100
Always negotiate I cannot emphasize this enough.

04:18.200 --> 04:24.000
See negotiation is is quite difficult and it is uncomfortable for most people.

04:24.000 --> 04:30.780
Actually I've never met somebody that just loves negotiating maybe one or two but negotiating is very

04:30.780 --> 04:37.950
tricky because it is very different between social dynamics and cultures and demographics appropriate

04:37.950 --> 04:44.400
advice for somebody in North America who's a white male maybe different than somebody in a completely

